
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Client
    participant Controller as AttachmentController
    participant AuthGuard
    participant Interceptor as FileUploadProcessingInterceptor
    participant Factory as FileUploadStrategyFactory
    participant Strategy as CloudinaryStrategy
    participant Service as AttachmentService
    participant MongoDB
    participant Redis

    Note over Client,Redis: 📤 Upload Single Attachment Flow

    Client->>Controller: POST /attachments/upload<br/>(multipart/form-data)
    activate Controller
    
    Controller->>AuthGuard: Validate JWT Token
    activate AuthGuard
    AuthGuard-->>Controller: UserPayload (authenticated)
    deactivate AuthGuard
    
    Controller->>Interceptor: Process File Upload
    activate Interceptor
    
    Interceptor->>Interceptor: Multer Memory Storage
    Interceptor->>Interceptor: Validate MIME Type & Size
    
    Interceptor->>Factory: Get Upload Strategy
    activate Factory
    Factory->>Factory: Check FILE_UPLOAD_STRATEGY env
    Factory-->>Interceptor: IFileUploadStrategy (Cloudinary)
    deactivate Factory
    
    Interceptor->>Strategy: uploadFile(file, folder)
    activate Strategy
    Strategy->>Strategy: Upload to Cloudinary API
    Strategy-->>Interceptor: { url, publicId, size, mimeType }
    deactivate Strategy
    deactivate Interceptor
    
    Interceptor-->>Controller: req.uploadedFiles = [attachmentIds]
    
    Controller->>Service: uploadSingleAttachment()
    activate Service
    
    Service->>Service: Detect File Type (image/video/document)
    Service->>Service: Create Attachment Document
    
    Service->>MongoDB: Insert Attachment Record
    activate MongoDB
    MongoDB-->>Service: { _id, attachment, attachmentType, ... }
    deactivate MongoDB
    
    Service->>Redis: SET attachment:{id} (TTL: 300s)
    activate Redis
    Redis-->>Service: OK
    deactivate Redis
    
    Service-->>Controller: Attachment ID
    deactivate Service
    
    Controller->>Controller: TransformResponseInterceptor
    Controller-->>Client: { success: true, attachmentIds: [...] }
    deactivate Controller

    Note over Client,Redis: 📥 Get Attachments Flow (with Caching)

    Client->>Controller: GET /attachments/by-entity?<br/>attachedToType=task&attachedToId=123
    activate Controller
    
    Controller->>Service: getAttachmentsByEntity()
    activate Service
    
    Service->>Redis: GET attachment:{id}
    activate Redis
    Redis-->>Service: null (Cache Miss)
    deactivate Redis
    
    Service->>MongoDB: Find { attachedToType, attachedToId, isDeleted: false }
    activate MongoDB
    MongoDB-->>Service: [AttachmentDocument[]]
    deactivate MongoDB
    
    Service->>Redis: SET attachment:{id} (TTL: 300s)
    activate Redis
    Redis-->>Service: OK
    deactivate Redis
    
    Service-->>Controller: [AttachmentDocument[]]
    deactivate Service
    
    Controller-->>Client: { data: [attachments] }
    deactivate Controller

    Note over Client,Redis: 🗑️ Delete Attachment Flow

    Client->>Controller: DELETE /attachments/:id
    activate Controller
    
    Controller->>Service: deleteAttachment(id)
    activate Service
    
    Service->>Service: Find Attachment by ID
    Service->>MongoDB: FindOne { _id: id }
    activate MongoDB
    MongoDB-->>Service: AttachmentDocument
    deactivate MongoDB
    
    Service->>Strategy: deleteFile(publicId)
    activate Strategy
    Strategy->>Strategy: Delete from Cloudinary
    Strategy-->>Service: Success
    deactivate Strategy
    
    Service->>MongoDB: UpdateOne { isDeleted: true, deletedAt: now }
    activate MongoDB
    MongoDB-->>Service: Acknowledged
    deactivate MongoDB
    
    Service->>Redis: DEL attachment:{id}
    activate Redis
    Redis-->>Service: OK
    deactivate Redis
    
    Service-->>Controller: Success
    deactivate Service
    
    Controller-->>Client: { message: "Attachment deleted successfully" }
    deactivate Controller

    Note over Client,Redis: ⚙️ Strategy Pattern Configuration

    rect rgb(240, 240, 240)
        Note over Factory: Environment Configuration
        Factory->>Factory: FILE_UPLOAD_STRATEGY = 'cloudinary' (default)<br/>or 's3' or 'digitalocean'
        
        alt Strategy: cloudinary
            Factory->>Strategy: CloudinaryStrategy
            Note over Strategy: Uses Cloudinary API<br/>Supports: images, videos
        else Strategy: s3
            Factory->>Strategy: S3Strategy
            Note over Strategy: Uses AWS SDK<br/>Supports: all file types
        else Strategy: digitalocean
            Factory->>Strategy: S3Strategy
            Note over Strategy: Uses DO Spaces API<br/>S3-compatible
        end
    end

